RACES on DarkWind

	There are ten races on DarkWind.  They are:  draconian, dwarf, elf,
faerie, gnome, halfling, human, ogre, orc, and troll.  Each of these
races has inherent advantages as well as drawbacks that typify
their racial attributes.  Choosing a race is very different than
choosing a guild.  Races generally involve small-scale effects of
encompassing aspects of your character.  Guilds generally involve large
scale abilities that are very specific in their use.
	Another note about races is that the good points and bad points
of each tend to negate each other, so that you are no better or
worse off choosing one over another, or choosing none at all (as in the
times before the Gods of DarkWind saw fit to bestow variety upon
the people of the realm).
	Most of what you will notice being a member of a specific race is
that you have more natural aptitude at certain kinds of attributes.  This
is reflected in the varied cost for your stats.  This is the most
noticeable effect.  There may be some other, very minor, talents
or abilities, as well.
	Note that the "say" command on Darkwind does not speak in the
common tongue, but in your own racial language.  You can learn other
races' languages, as well, so that other players' speech is more
comprehensible than an unintelligible mumble.
